# Git Commit Attribution

- Never add Cursor, Cursor Agent, or any AI tool as a commit author or co-author.
- Never add `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` or similar AI attribution to commit messages.
- Before completing a commit or release, verify the resulting commit message contains no Cursor or AI attribution.
- Preserve only human authorship information explicitly configured by the repository owner.
